/item
/info
/user



http methods 
------------

1.get - when we want to retrieve some data from server
2.post - when we want to create some data on server
3.put - when we want to update a data
4.delete - when we want to delete data
5.Patch - when we want to update data partially 




// Status code 

    -status codes are 3 digit numbers that tells you if a request was successful or failed and why
     200 - OK
     201 - created 
     400 - bad request
     401 - unauthorized
     404 - not found
     500 - internal server error 

Database 
    - SQL  - Structured Query Language
        - tabular format 
        - ACID properties 
    - NOSQL - Not Only Strucutured Query language
       - Document oriented (e.g - Mongodb)
       - Column oriented (e.g - Cassandra)
       - Key- value pair (e.g - Redis)
       - Graph oriented (e.g - Neo4j)
      

//mongodb 
   - BSON format
   - No sql database
   - faster than sql 
   - can handle large amount of data


 database
  - schema - logical description of the database



